3. Uses of Node.js
1. Web Server Development

Used to create web servers.

2. API Development

Used to build REST APIs and backend services.

3. Database Connectivity

Connects with databases like MongoDB and MySQL.

4. Real-Time Applications

Used for chat applications and live notifications.

5. Command Line Tools

Used to create terminal-based tools.

6. Backend Development

Handles business logic and server-side operations.

